   <text>
      <body>
         <pb/>
         <milestone n="50" unit="page"/>
         <lb/>
         <lb/>
         <head rend="ms.">
            <add hand="dw" rend="ink" resp="ww">
               <del>a
                                   Reverie</del>
            </add>
         </head>
         <lg n="1">
            <l n="1">Strange fits of passion I have known<del>,</del>
               <add place="rmargin" rend="ink" resp="ww">:/</add>
            </l>
            <l n="2">And I will dare to tell,</l>
            <l n="3">
               <add place="lmargin" rend="ink" resp="ww">/L</add> But in
                                   the <del>l</del>over’s ear alone,</l>
            <l n="4">What once to me befel.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="2">
            <l n="5">When she I lov’d, was strong and gay</l>
            <l n="6">And like a rose in June,</l>
            <l n="7">I to her cottage bent my way,</l>
            <l n="8">Beneath the evening <del>m</del>oon. <add place="rmargin" rend="ink" resp="ww">M/</add>
            </l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="3">
            <l n="9">
               <add place="lmargin" rend="ink" resp="ww">/M</add> Upon
                                   the <del>m</del>oon I fix’d my eye,</l>
            <l n="10">All over the wide lea<del>;</del>
               <add place="rmargin" rend="ink" resp="ww">:/</add>
            </l>
            <l n="11">
               <add place="lmargin" rend="ink" resp="ww">/H/—</add> My <del>h</del>orse trudg’d
                                   on^ and we drew nigh</l>
            <l n="12">Those paths so dear to me.</l>
         </lg>
         <pb/>
         <milestone n="51" unit="page"/>
         <lb/>
         <lb/>
         <lg n="4">
            <l n="13">And now we reach’d the orchard plot<del>,</del>
               <add place="rmargin" rend="ink" resp="ww">;/</add>
            </l>
            <l n="14">And, as we climb’d the hill,</l>
            <l n="15">Towards the roof of Lucy’s cot</l>
            <l n="16">
               <add place="lmargin" rend="ink" resp="ww">/M</add> The
                                        <del>m</del>oon descended still.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="5">
            <l n="17">In one of those sweet dreams I slept,</l>
            <l n="18">Kind Nature’s gentlest boon!</l>
            <l n="19">And, all the while, my eyes I kept</l>
            <l n="20">On the descending <del>m</del>oon. <add place="rmargin" rend="ink" resp="ww">M/</add>
            </l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="6">
            <l n="21">
               <add place="lmargin" rend="ink" resp="ww">/H</add> My
                                        <del>h</del>orse mov’d on; hoof after hoof</l>
            <l n="22">
               <add place="rmargin" rend="ink" resp="ww">/,</add>He
                                        rais’d<add place="belowline" rend="ink" resp="ww">^</add>and never stopp’d:</l>
            <l n="23">When down behind the cottage roof</l>
            <l n="24">
               <add place="lmargin" rend="ink" resp="ww">/P</add> At
                                   once the <del>p</del>lanet dropp’d.</l>
         </lg>
         <lg n="7">
            <l n="25">What fond and wayward thoughts will slide</l>
            <l n="26">Into a Lover’s head—</l>
            <l n="27">“O mercy!” to myself I cried,</l>
            <l n="28">“If Lucy should be dead!”</l>
         </lg>
      </body>
